  "description": "<p>The quintessential pack for the ambitious ski mountaineer or alpinist. This pack can be stripped down according to the mission at hand. Slim but far from frail, it blends a clean, body-hugging fit with construction that shrugs off the abuse of alpine travel. At 38L, it suits long approaches that start (and probably end) by the light of a headlamp, or technical objectives that demand a full gear arsenal.</p><ul><li>Lightweight, high-tenacity nylon has excellent abrasion resistance</li><li>Zippered lid with 2 litres of storage</li><li>Dual ice tool attachment for technical alpine and ice ascents</li><li>Side compression straps provide volume adjustment</li><li>Removable avalanche tool pouch</li><li>Front pocket holds a water flask</li><li>Helmet carry attachment. (Helmet Holder sold separately)</li><li>Easy access to the side of the pack with a full-length zipper</li><li>Removeable lightweight steel frame</li><li>Skimo-style, quick ski carry system plus A-frame carry</li><li>Pack weighs 980 grams or 883 grams without the frame and ski accessories</li></ul>",
